# ⚙️ COA Concept 3: Cache Coherence in Multicore Systems

We touched this earlier; now deeper.

---

## 1️⃣ Problem

Each core has its own cache.

One core updates data.

Other cores may still see old value.

---

## Example

```text id="2v8d4n"
Core1 → X = 10
Core2 → still sees X = 5
```

Wrong ❌

---

## Solution

Cache coherence protocols.

Most famous:

👉 MESI protocol

---

# MESI States (Basic Idea)

```text id="p0j7qa"
Modified
Exclusive
Shared
Invalid
```

Controls cache consistency.

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why cache coherence needed?**

👉 To maintain consistent data across multiple caches.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="w1q9ls"
Many caches → need consistency
```

